<h3 id="customize">Customize code templates</h3>
<p>To modify templates:</p>

<ol>
	<li>Turn on the "Live customization mode":</li>
	<img src="image/doc/customize/live/on.bmp">
	<li>Go to your store's frontend:</li>
	When the customization mode is on, you will notice how moving your mouse cursor affects distinct areas of your store's website. These are the chunks / parts of the the web site and each of them is controlled by a particular template thus to modify a part of your web site you have to alter appropriate template. When you locate the necessary template click on its name:
</ol>
<p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: You can also manage templates in the <a href="aa">Edit Templates</a> section where they are presented in a structured manner.</p>

<h3 id="translate">Translate GUI</h3>
<p>To translate user interface:</p>

<ol>
	<li>Turn on the "Live translation mode":</li>
	<img src="image/doc/customize/live/on.bmp">
	<li>Go to your store's frontend:</li>
	You should see a "translate" pop-up once you move mouse cursor around. To translate particular details of the user interface, drag your mouse cursor over a word or a phrase and click "translate". A translation box will appear ...
</ol>


